#: ../../../api.rst:117
msgid "Migrating to 1.x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:119
msgid ""
"This section details the main differences between 0.x and 1.x and is meant "
"to ease the pain of upgrading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:124 ../../../api.rst:221
msgid "API Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:126
msgid "``Response.json`` is now a callable and not a property of a response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:130
msgid ""
"import requests\n"
"r = requests.get('https://api.github.com/events')\n"
"r.json()   # This *call* raises an exception if JSON decoding fails"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:134
msgid ""
"The ``Session`` API has changed. Sessions objects no longer take parameters. "
"``Session`` is also now capitalized, but it can still be instantiated with a "
"lowercase ``session`` for backwards compatibility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:140
msgid ""
"s = requests.Session()    # formerly, session took parameters\n"
"s.auth = auth\n"
"s.headers.update(headers)\n"
"r = s.get('https://httpbin.org/headers')"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:145
msgid "All request hooks have been removed except 'response'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:147
msgid ""
"Authentication helpers have been broken out into separate modules. See "
"requests-oauthlib_ and requests-kerberos_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:153
msgid ""
"The parameter for streaming requests was changed from ``prefetch`` to "
"``stream`` and the logic was inverted. In addition, ``stream`` is now "
"required for raw response reading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:159
msgid ""
"# in 0.x, passing prefetch=False would accomplish the same thing\n"
"r = requests.get('https://api.github.com/events', stream=True)\n"
"for chunk in r.iter_content(8192):\n"
"    ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:164
msgid ""
"The ``config`` parameter to the requests method has been removed. Some of "
"these options are now configured on a ``Session`` such as keep-alive and "
"maximum number of redirects. The verbosity option should be handled by "
"configuring logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:171
msgid ""
"import requests\n"
"import logging\n"
"\n"
"# Enabling debugging at http.client level (requests->urllib3->http.client)\n"
"# you will see the REQUEST, including HEADERS and DATA, and RESPONSE with "
"HEADERS but without DATA.\n"
"# the only thing missing will be the response.body which is not logged.\n"
"try: # for Python 3\n"
"    from http.client import HTTPConnection\n"
"except ImportError:\n"
"    from httplib import HTTPConnection\n"
"HTTPConnection.debuglevel = 1\n"
"\n"
"logging.basicConfig() # you need to initialize logging, otherwise you will "
"not see anything from requests\n"
"logging.getLogger().setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n"
"requests_log = logging.getLogger(\"urllib3\")\n"
"requests_log.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)\n"
"requests_log.propagate = True\n"
"\n"
"requests.get('https://httpbin.org/headers')"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:194
msgid "Licensing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:196
msgid ""
"One key difference that has nothing to do with the API is a change in the "
"license from the ISC_ license to the `Apache 2.0`_ license. The Apache 2.0 "
"license ensures that contributions to Requests are also covered by the "
"Apache 2.0 license."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:206
msgid "Migrating to 2.x"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:209
msgid ""
"Compared with the 1.0 release, there were relatively few backwards "
"incompatible changes, but there are still a few issues to be aware of with "
"this major release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:213
msgid ""
"For more details on the changes in this release including new APIs, links to "
"the relevant GitHub issues and some of the bug fixes, read Cory's blog_ on "
"the subject."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:223
msgid ""
"There were a couple changes to how Requests handles exceptions. "
"``RequestException`` is now a subclass of ``IOError`` rather than "
"``RuntimeError`` as that more accurately categorizes the type of error. In "
"addition, an invalid URL escape sequence now raises a subclass of "
"``RequestException`` rather than a ``ValueError``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:231
msgid "requests.get('http://%zz/')   # raises requests.exceptions.InvalidURL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:233
msgid ""
"Lastly, ``httplib.IncompleteRead`` exceptions caused by incorrect chunked "
"encoding will now raise a Requests ``ChunkedEncodingError`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:236
msgid ""
"The proxy API has changed slightly. The scheme for a proxy URL is now "
"required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:241
msgid ""
"proxies = {\n"
"  \"http\": \"10.10.1.10:3128\",    # use http://10.10.1.10:3128 instead\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"# In requests 1.x, this was legal, in requests 2.x,\n"
"#  this raises requests.exceptions.MissingSchema\n"
"requests.get(\"http://example.org\", proxies=proxies)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:251
msgid "Behavioural Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:253
msgid ""
"Keys in the ``headers`` dictionary are now native strings on all Python "
"versions, i.e. bytestrings on Python 2 and unicode on Python 3. If the keys "
"are not native strings (unicode on Python 2 or bytestrings on Python 3) they "
"will be converted to the native string type assuming UTF-8 encoding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api.rst:258
msgid ""
"Values in the ``headers`` dictionary should always be strings. This has been "
"the project's position since before 1.0 but a recent change (since version "
"2.11.0) enforces this more strictly. It's advised to avoid passing header "
"values as unicode when possible."
msgstr ""
